tip.text: Large menu, but if it's your first time, you gotta go for the chicken & waffles combo.  Busy spot, so be prepared to wait. Servers are friendly too! Make sure you go there feeling hungry!

tip.text: Milk tea is good & nice spot to relax. There's WiFi too! Staff are friendly.
The udon is out of this world! The cold versions are so tasty if hot isn't your thing. Service was fantastic too. It's a busy spot, so be prepared to wait.

formattedAddress: 329 E 1st St (btwn San Pedro & Central Ave)

tip.text: Truffle white 🍕, throwback retro desserts, fish soup! The waiters are friendly & service is prompt.
The paella is amazing! The appetisers are so good too! Would recommend getting the white sangria. It's a busy restaurant, so expect to wait.
The brunch food is amazing! Definitely order a side of their onion rings too! There's a long wait for a table. The staff are really friendly. Order a drink while you wait.
Matcha latte was good & the mix icecream was yummy!
Quiet place central to have a tea or coffee & does has wifi. Food isn't great. There aren't many souvenirs you can buy, & most look super old.

formattedAddress: Gardens by the Bay (18 Marina Gardens Dr)

tip.text: A lovely selection of paintings from the Dutch masters through the ages. Wonderful examples of 17th century cabinets & antiquities. Don't wait in line for the coat check, use the lockers €1!
Good beers, the line is pretty long, but it's worth the wait. They also serve scotch eggs if you're feeling hungry. £3 deposit for a pint glass, so make sure you bring change! The Vienna is tasty!

venue.name: Tai Ping Koon Restaurant (太平館餐廳)

tip.text: Really beautiful grounds! Dog friendly outside of the palace. The palace interior was beautiful, but only one floor to walk in. The Ai weiwei exhibition was random & out of place in its surroundings.
